# Int16 overflow tests

(tx 'create schema test')
(tx 'create table test.item(field: int16)')
!tx 'insert (170141183460469231731687303715884105728) into test.item (field)'
---
> error[PO0001]: value overflows column `field` type `INT16`
>   1 │ insert (170141183460469231731687303715884105728) into test.item (field)
>     │         ^
>     = value `170141183460469231731687303715884105728` does not fit into `INT16` (range: -170141183460469231731687303715884105728 to 170141183460469231731687303715884105727)
> 
> note: column `field` is of type `INT16`
> 
> help: reduce the value, change the column type to a wider type or change the overflow policy
